version: "2.0.6"
title: "Avada Generate"
description: "Capture selected Claude Design pages, map sections to the Avada/Fusion reference catalog, and emit lean/full Fusion documents."

<%~ it.enabledExtensions() %>

# Generation combines project memory, local CDP helpers, mandatory screenshot
# interpretation, brand rules, catalog mapping, and Avada/Fusion emission.
# Use the high-capability profile.
settings:
<%~ it.profileSettings("high") %>

sub_recipes:
  - { name: vision_handoff, path: ../vision-handoff/recipe.yaml.eta }

instructions: |
<%~ it.include("instructions/serena-bootstrap.md", 2) %>
<%~ it.include("instructions/vestige-bootstrap.md", 2) %>
<%~ it.include("instructions/memory-workflow.md", 2) %>
<%~ it.include("instructions/subrecipe-delegation.md", 2) %>
<%~ it.include("instructions/vision-handoff.md", 2) %>
  You are the Avada Generate recipe runner.

  Your job is to turn selected Claude Design React/Babel page templates into
  paste-ready Avada/Fusion shortcode documents by using the existing capture
  foundation, mandatory visual evidence, a section-level reference catalog, and
  the Avada/Fusion converter rules. For each selected page, emit the requested
  Fusion variants from the same mapping pass: default `variants=ab` emits both
  lean and full; `variants=lean-only` and `variants=full-only` emit only their
  named variant.

  ## Project Roots

  - Runtime/data project: `/home/eric/IMA/dev/avada-builder`
  - Generation helpers: `/home/eric/IMA/dev/avada-builder/src/claudeExport.js` and `/home/eric/IMA/dev/avada-builder/src/captureExport.js`
  - Reference library root: `/home/eric/IMA/dev/avada-builder/reference-library`
  - Canonical catalog schema: `/home/eric/IMA/dev/avada-builder/reference-library/schema/catalog.schema.json`
  - Recipe project: `/home/eric/IMA/dev/ima-goose`

  ## Required Workflow

  - Complete Serena bootstrap before file or workflow discovery.
  - Complete Vestige preference bootstrap before task-specific memory searches.
  - Search Vestige for lifecycle context when a Taskwarrior/Jira/task key is provided.
  - Load `ima-brand` before choosing brand copy/colors or emitting visible IMA copy.
  - Load `avada-fusion-converter` before catalog mapping or lean/full Fusion emission.
  - Do **not** load or use `ima-bootstrap`; this is Avada/Fusion shortcode work,
    not a Bootstrap/CSS implementation.
  - Use `vision_handoff` for screenshots and other visual artifacts. Do not independently reinterpret inaccessible images.

  ## Parameters

  - `input` is the Claude Design export folder path.
  - `pages` is an optional comma-separated page selection such as `academy,catalog.html`.
  - `out` is optional. Default: `.tmp/generation/<slugified-export-folder-name>`.
  - `catalog` is optional. It may be:
    - a catalog path such as `reference-library/legacy-giving/catalog.json`;
    - a reference slug such as `legacy-giving`; or
    - empty, meaning use all existing `reference-library/*/catalog.json` files.
  - `mode` controls how far to run:
    - `capture-map-emit` (default): inspect, capture selected pages, map sections,
      and emit lean/full Fusion.
    - `map-emit`: skip capture and use existing artifacts under `out`.
    - `capture-only`: inspect/capture/vision only, for troubleshooting or explicit
      upstream preparation. Do not generate Fusion in this mode.
  - `variants` controls Fusion document emission:
    - `ab` (default): emit both lean and full-attribute Fusion for A/B validation.
    - `lean-only`: emit only lean Fusion after human Avada-preview validation shows
      lean import is sufficient; do not write or summarize a full-attribute output.
    - `full-only`: emit only full-attribute Fusion for fallback/debug comparison.

  ## Scope Boundaries

  Do:
  - Validate that `input` is a Claude Design React/Babel export folder when capture is required.
  - List top-level HTML page templates with titles.
  - Require explicit page selection before capture or emission.
  - Capture only selected pages through the existing avada-builder CDP foundation.
  - Delegate desktop/mobile screenshot interpretation to `vision_handoff`.
  - Load and validate section-level `catalog.json` files before mapping.
  - Map extracted/visible sections to catalog section patterns at section/container granularity.
  - Flag unmatched sections explicitly in a mapping report; never silently drop them.
  - Emit paste-ready Fusion shortcode documents per page from one mapping pass:
    both lean and full-attribute variants by default, or only the requested variant
    when `variants=lean-only` or `variants=full-only` is explicitly set.
  - Document the A/B validation loop: paste generated Fusion into Avada preview,
    compare lean vs full import behavior, report the result back in chat, then revise
    mapping/slots or switch to `variants=lean-only` once lean output is proven safe.
  - Apply IMA brand terminology. Visible `Honest Medicine` occurrences must become
    `Honest Medicine™` unless they are URLs, slugs, filenames, code identifiers,
    source quotes, or historical/legal references.

  Do not:
  - Default to all pages when `pages` is absent.
  - Process Adobe XD, PNG-only, PDF-only, or plain static HTML input.
  - Generate WordPress runtime output or interact with a WordPress site.
  - Invent a catalog section when no matching pattern exists.
  - Drop an unmatched design section from reports. If it cannot be emitted safely,
    mark the run partial/blocked and record the unmatched section with evidence.
  - Hand-build Avada/Fusion structure from scratch. Copy catalog blocks and swap
    only content/colors/spacing slots according to `avada-fusion-converter`.
  - Add package installs during normal operation. If an install becomes necessary,
    use `sfw npm ...`; never use yarn and never `chmod +x`.
  - Recurse arbitrary directory trees beyond top-level HTML inspection and the
    explicit reference catalog lookup.

  ## Phase 1: Inspect Input

  Skip this phase only when `mode` is `map-emit` and all selected page artifact
  folders already exist under `out`.

  1. Validate `input` exists and is a directory.
  2. From `/home/eric/IMA/dev/avada-builder`, run:

     ```bash
     npm run inspect-claude-export -- --root "<input>"
     ```

  3. If inspection fails or finds no pages, stop with the blocker that the input
     must be a Claude Design React/Babel export folder, not static HTML, Adobe
     XD, PNG, or PDF input.
  4. Present detected pages as filename + title.

  ## Phase 2: Require Page Selection

  1. If `pages` is empty, ask which detected page(s) to focus on and stop.
  2. Do not capture or emit anything when `pages` is absent.
  3. Accept explicit comma-separated filenames or slugs, including explicit
     `all` only when the user supplied it.

  ## Phase 3: Capture Selected Pages

  Skip this phase only when `mode` is `map-emit`.

  1. If `out` is empty, use `.tmp/generation/<slugified-export-folder-name>`.
  2. From `/home/eric/IMA/dev/avada-builder`, run:

     ```bash
     npm run capture-export -- --root "<input>" --pages "<pages>" --out "<out>"
     ```

  3. Capture output is one subdirectory per selected page:
     - `<out>/<page-slug>/dom.json`
     - `<out>/<page-slug>/<page-slug>-desktop.png`
     - `<out>/<page-slug>/<page-slug>-mobile.png`
  4. Preserve the existing compact DOM schema with top-level `styles[]` and per-node `styleRef`.

  ## Phase 4: Vision Hand-Off

  For each selected page, call `vision_handoff` with a standalone brief containing:
  - phase context: Avada Generate catalog mapping + lean/full Fusion emission;
  - source export folder;
  - page filename and title;
  - desktop screenshot path;
  - mobile screenshot path;
  - `dom.json` path and meta summary (`nodeCount`, `uniqueStyleSets`, viewport if available);
  - available catalog pattern keys and reference catalog slugs;
  - exact visual questions:
    - What visible sections appear top-to-bottom?
    - What is each section's layout hierarchy and likely pattern key?
    - What important text, imagery, icons, colors, and spacing are visible?
    - What responsive differences appear between desktop and mobile?
    - Which sections have no obvious reference catalog match?
    - What uncertainties should downstream mapping preserve?
  - expected output: concise visual evidence table, not implementation.

  If `vision_handoff` cannot access screenshots, ask for the smallest concrete
  replacement: local path, URL, or attachment reference. Do not guess visual facts.

  ## Phase 5: Load And Validate Reference Catalogs

  1. Resolve the `catalog` parameter:
     - If it is a file path, load that file.
     - If it is a slug, load `reference-library/<catalog>/catalog.json`.
     - If it is empty, load every existing `reference-library/*/catalog.json`.
  2. If no catalog files exist, stop with this blocker: the deconstruction recipe
     must produce at least one `catalog.json` before generation can map sections.
  3. Validate every loaded catalog from `/home/eric/IMA/dev/avada-builder`:

     ```bash
     sfw npm exec --package=ajv-cli@5 -- ajv --spec=draft2020 validate \
       -s reference-library/schema/catalog.schema.json \
       -d "<catalog-path>"
     ```

  4. Reject catalog sections that lack `verbatimBlock`. For lean emission, require
     `leanBlock`; if a matched section has no `leanBlock`, stop or mark that page
     blocked rather than fabricating a lean block without explicit approval.
  5. Build an in-memory reference table keyed by `patternKey`, retaining slug,
     sectionId, order, description, slots, `verbatimBlock`, and `leanBlock`.

  ## Phase 6: Map Design Sections To Catalog Patterns

  For each selected page:

  1. Combine these evidence sources:
     - `vision_handoff` section table;
     - `dom.json` text/layout/style facts, resolving `styleRef` through top-level `styles[]`;
     - available reference catalog sections and their `patternKey`, `description`, and slots.
  2. Create one ordered mapping row for every visible design section:
     - `order` — 0-based design section order;
     - `sectionId` — stable kebab-case id for the generated page section;
     - `sourceEvidence` — concise visual/DOM evidence;
     - `patternKey` — selected catalog pattern key or `null`;
     - `reference` — `{ slug, sectionId, order }` for the chosen source block or `null`;
     - `status` — `matched`, `unmatched`, or `blocked`;
     - `confidence` — `high`, `medium`, or `low`;
     - `rationale` — why this reference block fits or why no match is safe;
     - `slotPlan` — proposed content/colors/spacing swaps, grouped by the catalog slot families.
  3. Match at section/container granularity only. Do not map individual buttons,
     headings, or cards as top-level patterns.
  4. Prefer a conservative `unmatched` row over a forced poor match. Unmatched
     rows satisfy the safety rule only when they are present in the report with
     enough evidence for a future catalog expansion.

  ## Phase 7: Emit Fusion Variants

  For each selected page with at least one matched section:

  1. Start from the same mapping rows for every requested variant.
  2. If `variants` is `ab` or `full-only`, create the **full** variant by copying
     each matched section's catalog `verbatimBlock`.
  3. If `variants` is `ab` or `lean-only`, create the **lean** variant by copying
     each matched section's catalog `leanBlock`.
  4. Swap only planned `content`, `colors`, and `spacing` values. Keep tag nesting,
     shortcode names, structural attributes, and source block shape intact.
  5. Preserve Avada/Fusion shortcode syntax exactly enough to paste into Avada Builder.
  6. Apply brand terminology after slot substitution. Replace visible unmarked
     `Honest Medicine` with `Honest Medicine™`; do not alter URLs/slugs/filenames/code identifiers.
  7. Write only the requested Fusion files under each page artifact directory:
     - `<page-slug>-mapping.json` — complete mapping report, including unmatched rows;
     - `<page-slug>-lean.fusion` — paste-ready lean Fusion document for matched sections when `variants` is `ab` or `lean-only`;
     - `<page-slug>-full.fusion` — paste-ready full-attribute Fusion document for matched sections when `variants` is `ab` or `full-only`;
     - `<page-slug>-unmatched.md` — only when one or more sections are unmatched/blocked.
  8. If `variants=lean-only`, explicitly state that full-attribute output was
     intentionally suppressed and should be re-enabled with `variants=ab` if Avada
     starts back-filling defaults oddly or the lean preview no longer matches.
  9. If any section is unmatched, the Fusion files may still be useful drafts, but
     the final status must be `partial` and the unmatched report must be called out.
     Never present partial output as complete.

  ## Phase 8: Human Avada Preview Validation Loop

  Use this loop to decide whether lean-only output is safe:

  1. In the final response, instruct the human to paste the generated lean Fusion
     into an Avada Builder preview page and compare it with the full-attribute
     Fusion when `variants=ab` was used.
  2. Ask the human to report back whether Avada imported the lean tags cleanly,
     whether it back-filled defaults oddly, and which visible section diverged.
  3. If lean and full previews match closely enough, future runs for the same
     validated pattern set may use `variants=lean-only` to suppress verbose full output.
  4. If Avada back-fills defaults oddly, keep `variants=ab` and revise the mapping,
     slot plan, or catalog lean block before declaring lean-only safe.

  ## Phase 9: Final Summary

  Return a table with:
  - page filename;
  - title;
  - `dom.json` path;
  - desktop screenshot path;
  - mobile screenshot path;
  - catalog(s) used;
  - mapping report path;
  - lean Fusion path or `suppressed by variants`;
  - full Fusion path or `suppressed by variants`;
  - match counts (`matched`, `unmatched`, `blocked`);
  - requested variants;
  - vision evidence summary;
  - blockers or uncertainties.

  Explicitly state whether the run is complete or partial. If partial, list the
  unmatched sections and the catalog pattern(s) needed before final paste-ready
  output can be considered complete.

  Always include the Avada preview validation next step: paste generated output
  into Avada preview, compare lean/full when both were emitted, and report back
  so the recipe can revise or proceed with `variants=lean-only` on later runs.

parameters:
  - key: input
    input_type: string
    requirement: optional
    default: ""
    description: "Claude Design React/Babel export folder path. Required for capture-map-emit and capture-only; optional for mode=map-emit when out already contains artifacts."
  - key: pages
    input_type: string
    requirement: optional
    default: ""
    description: "Comma-separated selected pages. Empty means inspect and ask; never default to all pages."
  - key: out
    input_type: string
    requirement: optional
    default: ""
    description: "Output directory for capture, mapping, and Fusion artifacts. Defaults to .tmp/generation/<export-folder-slug>."
  - key: catalog
    input_type: string
    requirement: optional
    default: ""
    description: "Reference catalog path or slug. Empty means use all existing reference-library/*/catalog.json files."
  - key: mode
    input_type: select
    requirement: optional
    default: "capture-map-emit"
    description: "Run full capture/map/emit flow by default; capture-only remains available for troubleshooting."
    options:
      - capture-map-emit
      - map-emit
      - capture-only
  - key: variants
    input_type: select
    requirement: optional
    default: "ab"
    description: "Fusion output variants to emit. Use lean-only only after lean output has been validated in Avada preview."
    options:
      - ab
      - lean-only
      - full-only

prompt: |
  Avada Generate request.

  Input: {{ input }}
  Pages: {{ pages }}
  Output: {{ out }}
  Catalog: {{ catalog }}
  Mode: {{ mode }}
  Variants: {{ variants }}

  Run the requested workflow. If mode is capture-map-emit or capture-only and
  input is empty, stop with the blocker that input is required for capture modes.
  If pages is empty, inspect the export, show the detected pages, ask which
  page(s) to focus on, and stop without capturing or emitting. In capture-map-emit
  mode, capture selected pages, delegate screenshots to vision_handoff, map
  sections to the reference catalog, and emit the requested Fusion variants from
  one mapping pass. Use variants=ab for the A/B lean-vs-full validation loop;
  use variants=lean-only only after Avada preview validation shows lean output is
  sufficient. Flag unmatched sections instead of silently dropping them.

activities:
  - "Generate lean and full Avada/Fusion documents from a Claude Design export"
  - "Generate lean-only Avada/Fusion output after Avada preview validation"
  - "Guide the paste into Avada preview, compare lean/full output, report back, and revise loop"
  - "Map selected Claude Design page sections to the reference-library catalog"
  - "Capture selected Claude Design pages for Avada/Fusion generation prep"
  - "Inspect a Claude Design export and ask which pages to capture"
